  <sect2 role="package">
    <title>Introduo a KMix</title>

    <para>
      The <application>KMix</application> package contains a KF5 based Sound Mixer
application.
    </para>

    &lfs113_checked;

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Informao do Pacote</bridgehead>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Transferncia (HTTP): <ulink url="&kmix5-download-http;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Transferncia (FTP): <ulink url="&kmix5-download-ftp;"/>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Soma de verificao MD5: &kmix5-md5sum;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Tamanho da transferncia: &kmix5-size;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Espao em disco estimado exigido: &kmix5-buildsize;
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Tempo de construo estimado: &kmix5-time;
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Dependncias de KMix</bridgehead>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Exigida</bridgehead>
    <para role="required">
      <xref linkend="kf5-frameworks"/>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Recomendada</bridgehead>
    <para role="recommended">
      <xref linkend="alsa-lib"/>
    </para>

    <bridgehead renderas="sect4">Opcionais</bridgehead>
    <para role="optional">
      <xref linkend="libcanberra"/> and <xref linkend="pulseaudio"/>
    </para>

    <para condition="html" role="usernotes">
      Observaes de Usurio(a): <ulink url="&blfs-wiki;/kmix5"/>
    </para>
  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Instalao de KMix</title>

    <para>
      Instale <application>KMix</application> executando os seguintes comandos:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$KF5_PREFIX \
      -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release         \
      -DBUILD_TESTING=OFF                \
      -Wno-dev .. &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Esse pacote no vem com uma sute de teste.
    </para>

    <para>
      Agora, como o(a) usurio(a) <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem>:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>



